<!-- About Us -->
<section id="about" class="container py-5">
  <h2 class="section-title">About Us</h2>
  <p class="mt-3">Nofesh, the Hebrew word for "rest" or "vacation," was born from a longing to create a calm, minimalist escape from the noise of city life. We dreamed of a place that embraced silence, warmth, and simplicity—where nature and comfort embrace you in quiet elegance.
  </p>
  <p>We chose the name "Nofesh" because it evokes peace at first sound. It is a word you can feel exhaling from your chest, just like the sigh of relief when you settle into a soft bed after a long journey.</p>
  <p>What can you expect? A homey boutique space designed with warm wood, neutral tones, and sun-kissed textures. Rooms where you can breathe. Personal touches. No clutter—just calm. Our aim is to become your hidden sanctuary in Lagos.</p>
</section>

